{"lemma":"شاقَّةٍ","slug":"شاقَّةٍ","root":"ش.ق.ق","root_slug":"ش-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ق-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شاقّ","root":"شقق","pos":"V","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22691"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to excite desire in"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to please, to delight"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set up, to tie","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go against, to oppose, to clash with, to contend with"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to defy, to disobey, to rebel against"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of شَاقَّ (šāqqa)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"hard, arduous, laborious, toilsome","examples":[{"text":"الفَطُورُ الشَّامِلُ هُوَ المُكَافَأَةُ الْمِثَالِيَّةُ بَعْدَ تَمْرِينٍ شَاقٍّ.","english":"A full breakfast is a perfect reward after a tough workout."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of شَوْق (šawq)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22691","headword_ar":"شاقّهُ","root":"$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$aAq~apN","text_ar":"مُشَاقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iqaAqN","text_ar":"شِقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) the latter inf. n. occurring in the Kur ii. 131 and iv. 39 [&c.], (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted with him contrariously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adversely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and inimically;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of them doing to the other that which was distressing, grievous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"troublesome, so that each of them was in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~","text_ar":"شِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other than that of his fellow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he became in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~","text_ar":"شِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side, in respect of him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) accord. to Er-Rághib, the inf. n. signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~","text_ar":"شِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other than that of one's fellow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~u AlEaSaA bayonaka","text_ar":"شَقُّ العَصَا بَيْنَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabayona SaAHibika","text_ar":"وَبَيْنَ صَاحِبِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning “ the effecting disunion and dissension between thee and thy fellow ”], so that it is tropical: (TA:) or the primary meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iqaAqu","text_ar":"الشِّقَاقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the being"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mutually"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 326.) See also 1, in the first quarter of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":["M","Mgh","Msb","S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}